My Future IoT Project Idea

For my next project, I would like to expand my previous work into a more practical system called a Room Comfort Detector.

🔧 Components:

DHT22 (Temperature & Humidity Sensor)
LDR (Light Sensor)
ESP32 Microcontroller
LEDs / Buzzer for alerts
Wi-Fi module (for cloud integration)
              
⚙️ Working:

The system will continuously monitor room conditions such as temperature, humidity, and light intensity. 
              Based on predefined comfort ranges, it will determine whether the environment is comfortable or not.

If temperature is too high → suggest cooling (AC/fan)
If humidity is too low/high → suggest humidifier/dehumidifier
If lighting is insufficient → turn on lights

The system can also send data to a cloud dashboard using MQTT or HTTP, allowing users to monitor conditions remotely. 
Alerts can be triggered when conditions go outside the comfort zone.

🌍 Application:

This system can be used in homes, offices, and classrooms to maintain a comfortable and healthy indoor environment. 
It can also help in improving productivity and energy efficiency.
